      <hedline>
        <hl1>From a Couch Potato, Another Way to Surf</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mildren Marmur letter on May 21 article recalls retort to friend in Del Mar, Calif, who tried to encourage surfing (S)0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>With reference to the article ''You Don't Surf? You Can Still Look the Part'' (May 21), some years ago, I was visiting a friend in Del Mar, Calif., who kept encouraging me -- the couch potato who flunked gym in Brooklyn College -- to try the activity.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>With reference to the article ''You Don't Surf? You Can Still Look the Part'' (May 21), some years ago, I was visiting a friend in Del Mar, Calif., who kept encouraging me -- the couch potato who flunked gym in Brooklyn College -- to try the activity.</p>
        <p>I finally told her, ''They also surf who only stand and wade.''</p>
        <p>MILDREN MARMUR  Larchmont</p>
      </block>
